# Moltbot MVP — Sustainability & Scalability Analysis (v3)

> **Revised**: OpenClaw is the core agent framework and stays. Plan focuses on switching from CLI spawning to OpenClaw's Gateway/API mode. Haiku and JWT removed from scope.

---

## 1. Architecture Overview

```mermaid
graph LR
    A["Peppi (Laravel)"] -->|POST /execute-action| B["moltbot-fastapi<br/>Python/FastAPI<br/>Pro Plan"]
    B -->|POST /execute| C["openclaw-gateway<br/>Node.js/Express<br/>Pro Plan + Disk"]
    C -->|"spawn child_process<br/>(⚠️ bottleneck)"| D["openclaw CLI<br/>--local --message"]
    D -->|LLM reasoning| E["Gemini 2.5 Pro"]
    D -->|skill: bash + curl| F["Google APIs"]
    D -->|skill: bash + curl| B2["FastAPI /reminders/*"]
    B -->|sessions + locks| G["Upstash Redis"]
    B -->|credentials + logs| H["Supabase Postgres"]
    I["QStash"] -->|webhook| B3["FastAPI /reminders/deliver"]
    B3 -->|SMS| J["Peppi Outbound"]
    K["SearXNG"] -.->|web search| D
```

### Why OpenClaw Cannot Be Removed

OpenClaw is **not just a CLI wrapper** — it's the agent framework that:

| Capability | What OpenClaw Provides | Without It |
|-----------|----------------------|------------|
| **Skill Execution** | Reads SKILL.md files, gives the LLM bash/curl tools to execute | LLM can't execute any commands |
| **Tool Reasoning** | The LLM understands *when* and *how* to invoke skills | Raw LLM API has no tool chaining |
| **Session Memory** | Per-user conversation memory with `per-peer` scope | You'd rebuild this from scratch |
| **Multi-turn Context** | Carries context across tool calls within one request | LLM forgets between API calls |
| **System Prompt** | Injects SOUL.md automatically every turn | Manual prompt management |

**The LLM alone doesn't know how to use your skills. OpenClaw's agent architecture is what bridges LLM reasoning → skill execution → response.**

---

## 2. The Actual Problem: CLI Spawning

### Current Flow (Spawn per Request)

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant GW as Gateway (server.js)
    participant CLI as openclaw CLI (new process)
    participant LLM as Gemini 2.5 Pro

    GW->>CLI: child_process.spawn("openclaw agent --local --message ...")
    Note over CLI: ~200-400MB RAM per process
    CLI->>LLM: Send prompt + skills + context
    LLM->>CLI: Response (5-30 seconds)
    CLI->>GW: stdout JSON
    Note over CLI: Process dies
```

**Problem**: Each request creates a brand new OS process (~200-400MB RAM). With 4GB on Pro plan, max ~10-15 concurrent requests before OOM.

### The Fix: OpenClaw Gateway Daemon Mode

OpenClaw has a built-in **Gateway (daemon)** mode — a persistent HTTP API server that:
- Runs as a single long-lived process
- Manages sessions internally
- Executes skills in the same process
- Accepts HTTP requests instead of requiring CLI spawn

Your [server.js](file:///e:/Peppi/moltbot-render/moltbot-gateway/server.js) already has this comment at line 216:
```javascript
// Use --local to run the embedded agent directly with shell env vars.
// This avoids the "gateway closed" errors seen with the background daemon.
```

This tells us you **tried the daemon before** and hit "gateway closed" errors, which is why you fell back to `--local` (CLI spawn). The fix is to properly configure and stabilize the daemon mode.

### Target Architecture (Gateway Daemon Mode)

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant GW as Gateway (server.js)
    participant OC as OpenClaw Daemon (persistent)
    participant LLM as Gemini 2.5 Pro

    Note over OC: Started once, stays alive
    GW->>OC: HTTP POST /api/message (lightweight)
    OC->>LLM: Send prompt + skills + context
    LLM->>OC: Response
    OC->>GW: HTTP response
    Note over OC: Process stays alive, sessions in memory
```

**Benefits**:
- **No process spawn overhead** — OpenClaw daemon is always running
- **Shared memory** — sessions loaded once, reused across requests
- **~10x less RAM per request** — no new process per request
- **Faster cold start** — skills already loaded in memory

