### 🟠 Stage 2: OpenClaw Gateway Optimization (50-200 Users, 1-2 Months)

**Goal**: Switch from CLI spawn to OpenClaw's daemon/API mode. Remove the persistent disk. Enable autoscaling.

| # | Change | Where | Effort | Impact |
|---|--------|-------|--------|--------|
| 1 | **Add request queue/limiter in Gateway** — cap concurrent OpenClaw processes to prevent OOM | [server.js](file:///e:/Peppi/moltbot-render/moltbot-gateway/server.js) (add `MAX_CONCURRENT` check) | Small | Prevents crashes |
| 2 | **Fix OpenClaw Gateway daemon "gateway closed" errors** — investigate and stabilize daemon mode | OpenClaw config + [server.js](file:///e:/Peppi/moltbot-render/moltbot-gateway/server.js) | Medium | Unblocks daemon mode |
| 3 | **Switch [server.js](file:///e:/Peppi/moltbot-render/moltbot-gateway/server.js) from CLI spawn to HTTP calls** — call daemon's HTTP API instead of `child_process.spawn` | [server.js](file:///e:/Peppi/moltbot-render/moltbot-gateway/server.js) (rewrite [executeOpenClaw()](file:///e:/Peppi/moltbot-render/moltbot-gateway/server.js#185-413)) | Medium | Eliminates spawn overhead |
| 4 | **Move OpenClaw sessions/memory to Redis** — remove dependency on persistent disk | OpenClaw config + Redis setup | Medium | Enables autoscaling |
| 5 | **Remove persistent disk from [render.yaml](file:///e:/Peppi/moltbot-render/render.yaml)** | [render.yaml](file:///e:/Peppi/moltbot-render/render.yaml) L107-109 | Small | Unblocks autoscaling |
| 6 | **Enable Gateway autoscaling** on Render | Render Dashboard | Small | Horizontal scaling |
| 7 | **Enable FastAPI autoscaling** on Render | Render Dashboard | Small | Horizontal scaling |
| 8 | **Add API response caching** for common queries | [redis_client.py](file:///e:/Peppi/moltbot-render/fastapi-wrapper/app/core/redis_client.py) or Gateway | Small | Reduces LLM calls |
| 9 | **Set up staging environment** | [render.yaml](file:///e:/Peppi/moltbot-render/render.yaml) (staging services) | Medium | Safe testing |
| 10 | **Add basic CI/CD** (lint + deploy) | `.github/workflows/` | Small | Code quality |

**Change #1 Detail — Request queue in [server.js](file:///e:/Peppi/moltbot-render/moltbot-gateway/server.js):**
```javascript
const MAX_CONCURRENT = 8; // Leave buffer for Node.js + OS
let activeProcesses = 0;

app.post('/execute', async (req, res) => {
  if (activeProcesses >= MAX_CONCURRENT) {
    return res.status(503).json({ 
      error: 'Server busy', retryable: true 
    });
  }
  activeProcesses++;
  try { /* existing logic */ } 
  finally { activeProcesses--; }
});
```

**Change #3 Detail — Daemon mode in [server.js](file:///e:/Peppi/moltbot-render/moltbot-gateway/server.js):**
```javascript
// BEFORE: spawn new process per request
const openclaw = spawn('openclaw', ['agent', '--local', '--message', msg]);

// AFTER: HTTP call to persistent daemon
const response = await axios.post('http://localhost:3333/api/message', {
  message: msg,
  to: `agent:main:api:moltbot:dm:user_${userId}`,
  env: { GOOGLE_ACCESS_TOKEN: token, USER_TIMEZONE: tz }
});
```

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Change #2 is the most critical research task.** You need to investigate why the daemon gave "gateway closed" errors previously. Common causes:
> - Daemon not started before [server.js](file:///e:/Peppi/moltbot-render/moltbot-gateway/server.js) accepts requests
> - Daemon dying due to unhandled errors (no restart policy)
> - Session/memory corruption on disk
> - Network timeout between Express and daemon
> 
> Once the daemon runs stably, Changes #3-6 follow naturally.

**After Stage 2**: ~50-80 concurrent users, horizontally scalable.

